27/02/2022, 6:57â€¯pm - +91 6291 252 737: Campus Ambassador

Job description

The Campus Ambassador's day-to-day responsibilities include:

1. Creating awareness about Nordic Academy programs and events in your respective campuses, circle, and neighbourhood
2. Promoting Nordic Academy events on all possible online platforms/channels/groups/pages of Facebook, Instagram, Twitter, LinkedIn, and YouTube
3. Leveraging college official/unofficial channels to spread awareness about Nordic Academy events
4. Connecting to student groups of your college/other colleges
5. Collecting feedback and share new ideas from the university's community with us

Learning opportunities
1. Training sessions organized to train the Campus Ambassadors
2. Develop a powerful, scalable, and proficient sales model under the guidance of industry experts, a rare experience for a campus student
3. An opportunity to get connected with a network of corporate influencers across industries


Rewards and incentives
1. Commission per referral
// This is what Nordic Academy CRs make per month on an average;
Minimum: 3k - 3.5k
Average: 7k - 7.5k
Highest(till 31st Aug'21): 29k
2. 15% personal discount on all Nordic Academy programs
3. Certificates of Internship/LORs

Perks
Certificate
Letter of recommendation
Flexible timings.

07/03/2022, 3:40â€¯pm - Smruti Sanjeet (College): Dear All,                                                           *Greetings!*                                                                 To promote the importance of walkability, School Of Sustainability in collaboration with Ecospace Club is launching the walkability track today. The track starts at the UG hostel and makes its way around the IC to the main gate, around the parking lot to the Chapel, and back to the UG hostel. This distance burns around 100 kcal over 1.9km. Each junction has an indication of your calories lost, along with footsteps and memes to cheer you up.  
As a part of the inauguration event, we are organizing a challenge called "Greatest Loser Wins "from the 7th of March 2022 to the 8th of April 2022.  Wherein we keep a track of the participants who lose the most weight by walking on the prescribed track and whoever loses the most will be rewarded generously. The competition is open to all including students, staff, and faculty members to encourage maximum participation. 
Date: 7th of March 2022
Time: 4:30-5:30 pm 
Venue: Near UG Residence
Registration link: https://forms.gle/rSfyL4QNfpqux6gX6
Details: 
1. You can register through the google form link or can opt for walk-in registrations on the 7th of March 2022 4:30 pm to 5:30 pm. 
2. With your due consent, we will be taking your weight and height measurements for calculating your BMI for award consideration, but you can also take part voluntarily. 
3. The winners will be declared on the 8th of April, which is World Health Day solely on the basis of weight loss and consistent efforts. 
4. You will be briefed with the rest of the details on spot. 
5. In order to keep the spirit of dedication amongst the participants we would be charging Rs 1. as the registration fees.
See you soon on the path to healthy living. 
Have a pleasant Day                                           Thank you with regards.

12/03/2022, 8:50â€¯am - Smruti Sanjeet (College): Greetings from SportsHub!

With utmost vehemence and enlivened spirits, we are beyond elated to get the ball rolling for the annual flagship sports fest of the undergraduate wing of XIM University, "XEST-2022". Over the years, XEST has upheld the ideals of sportsmanship & camaraderie and has been instrumental in keeping the strong cultural and social fabric intact within the students of the University. Therefore, carrying the legacy forward, SportsHub- the UG sports committee, brings forward the biggest and most-awaited event of this year, certainly believing that this year's edition would surpass all the previously set benchmarks!

"So, shoes all buckled up?"

The entire annual sports fiesta comprises of 9 sporting events-
Cricket- boys and girls
Football
Volleyball
Kabaddi
Badminton- boys and girls
Basketball- boys and girls
Tennis- boys and girls
Throwball - only girls
E-sports (Valorant and BGMI)

**NOTE**
Students can select a maximum of 2 sports -- excluding e-sports (i.e Valorant and BGMI) 
A player will be subject to disqualification if they choose more than 2 sports -- excluding e-sports.
The participants can choose only one of the 2 e-sports (either BGMI or Valorant)

Please find the links to Participation, X-COPS and T-Shirts:

LINK FOR PARTICIPATION (ON-FIELD SPORTS):
https://forms.gle/kRXQqRNpi2wMJZCw6

LINK FOR PARTICIPATION (E-SPORTS):
https://forms.gle/vkucY4VQMgC6rPcM6

LINK FOR X-COPS:
https://forms.gle/o9pGokrd5vjzDYJs8

LINK FOR OFFICIAL XEST 2022 T-SHIRTS:
https://forms.gle/RZ7Ak9APrikK3vyG6

**NOTE**
Last date of the submission of the google form for participation and X-COPS is 12th March'22 - 5:00 p.m.
Last date for booking your official XEST-2022 T-shirt is 15th March'22 - 11:59 pm 
Students having the XEST-2022 official merchandise shall enjoy the perks on the D-day.
Please find the RULEBOOKS of all the sports events attached below.

As the SAC fees for the academic year 2021-22 have not been collected, we, therefore, encourage you all to buy the "XEST-2022" official merchandise T-shirts to celebrate the week-long fest in one accord! Looking forward to making this event a huge success with your best wishes and cooperation!

Rules to be followed on the freshers day:
1. No outside food/water/drink is allowed inside the mini auditorium.

We hope this mail finds you well and safe.

XCSE RenderHouse: The Video Editing and Graphic Designing Team of the School of Computer Science & Engineering, XIM University, is glad to announce the opening of membership for our team.
We aim to form a group of XCSE students curious about photography, video editing, and graphic designing to maximize the department's promotion.
The team concentrates on providing the students a platform to hone their skills and help them take a leap forward to broaden their knowledge within the domain of video editing, photography/videography, and graphic designing. Its objective will be to create promotional content for our department, for upcoming events, highlighting the subsequent:

1. The culture and values of XCSE
2. Events and Activities
3. Infrastructure and Facilities
4. Academic curriculum and Achievements
5. Experiences of both students and faculties.

Interested students can fill out the appended form to be a part of the team, 

Fill out the form here:
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSd4P3LsVJCohXcCz0DuB85WCEMl4sBXJo2XwmV3mrpuWKZpXg/viewform


We look forward to your active participation and a fantastic response for the same. Looking forward to working with you and having a journey.

24/07/2022, 7:15â€¯pm - Ipsita: Warm Greetings to all!!!

On the Occasion of World Nature Conservation Day - 28th July 2022, NSS Unit-II is collaborating with XPOSURE - The Photography Club in conducting a Photography Contest for the students. We hereby invite you to participate in the competition. Winners will be Awarded and all participants will be given Merit certificates.
Round 2 will be held offline where Top 5 contestants will be judged based on their skills. Refer to the Rule Book for further details.

Founder of Lenscape and recipient of the Biju Patnaik Award for Wildlife Conservation, Mr. Saswat Pati will judge the photographs for Round 1 and Round 2 (Final Round). Being a proud alumni from School of Communications, XIM University, he has spent countless hours developing, polishing, and expanding his skills as a professional photographer and decided to share them with the world. He has successfully completed several projects for significant clients such as  World Wildlife Fund, Tata Steel, Sightwavers, Coca Cola, Curly Tales, XIM University, Save the Children, Co Ops, German TV- ARD, Vedanta, France 24, Human Life Centre, Pradan, Govt of Odisha, BISLD.

Note: 

The Theme of the competition for Round 1 is mentioned in the event poster attached.

Rules have been attached in the form of (.PDF). Please go through the Rules once before clicking photographs.

Regardless of the device used, students are free to take pictures with Mobile Phones/ DSLRs or Mirrorless Cameras.

For further queries please feel free to contact the POCs through WhatsApp or Phone Calls.

You can enter the competition by filling out the Registration Form below and uploading your photographs in the same. The Top 5 participants who qualify for Round 2 will be contacted through WhatsApp and e-mail communication.

Register HERE: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1eel7r11HuviqBXyZ3BU7rWlPbGEtyoYbdk03w3toXhM/edit

We look forward to having you all with us and being our mainstay.

13/10/2022, 9:21â€¯am - Smruti Sanjeet (College): 'Everyone is beautiful and unique in their own way'
All of us have come across this phrase at some point of our lives, but the question is , do we really believe in it!? If not, then here's a chance for you to accept and spread this essence to yourself as well as to your loved one's :)

"Project Kaya" aims to spread love and kindness by reminding people that heterogeneity among the society doesn't create differences, instead it brings us together. Different genders, different colours, different sexualities all converge to one: which is us being simply humans. Hence it's our responsibility to love, respect and accept all humans irrespective of the community they belong to:)

To celebrate this thought 
"Project KAYA" welcomes you to be the part of its very first MCN fellowship event *"JASHN-E-FANKAAR"* where we celebrate all the artists including writers, poets, painters along with their art pieces,poetries and paintings!
.
.
.
.
The rules for the competition are pretty simple:
1. Every participant needs to rename their file in the form of(name_category) before submitting
2. All artwork submissions need to be in .jpeg form.
3. All article writing and poetry should be submitted in .pdf format.
4. The last date of submission is 13th October
5. A participant can submit multiple artworks and articles.
6. The winners will be announced online through a seminar.
7. The winners will be getting certificates.

Registration form- 
https://forms.gle/oHYfmzUAsFYbieV3A

For further reference about ' KAYA' do check your mails.
We would love to have you with us in this journey of ours!

18/03/2023, 9:30â€¯pm - Smruti Sanjeet (College): Dear Residents,

This message is to inform every resident regarding the precautionary safety measures before leaving the residence premises for leave.

Kindly adhere to the following instructions given below:

1. An individual resident is accountable for their personal and valuable belongings.

2. All the doors and windows shall be closed properly before leaving the residence.

3. All the fans, lights and other switches must be turned off.

4. Every resident must sign the leave register kept at the reception (UG/IC/PG) before leaving the residence and submit the leave application form (pink form)

Residents who fails to sign the leave register kept at the reception (UG/IC/PG) may not be allowed at the main gate on the time of arrival.

NB: The RMT shall not be responsible for any loss of valuable or personal belongings.

Thank you. Happy and safe vacation.

Regards,
UG RSEC TEAM. (2023-24)
XIM UNIVERSITY | BHUBANESWAR.

The past year we successfully organised various events including e-sports, dance, music, quizzes and much more. We look forward to expanding our family and hence we're delighted to announce membership opening for all SCSE students. 

This term we have dissolved RenderHouse and aim to work with Video Editing and Graphic Designing enthusiasts as one team that is the Media Cell of our school.

*Membership privileges :-*
- All the events organised throughout the year are free for the members.
- Certification and Identification as a part of the Media Cell, School of Computer Science and Engineering.
- Planning and Organising Events, hence expanding network and building communication skills.
- Hands on graphic designing and video editing. 

*Membership rules :-*
1. Every member has to deposit a joining fee of Rs 80/- per year. (PhonePe/GPay number - 8280330535)
2. The core members will be from the foremost years i.e 2nd, 3rd, and 4th yrs.
3. After a continuous assessment the members will be promoted on the basis of your entire year performance.

13/05/2023, 11:42â€¯pm - Smruti Sanjeet (College): Dear colleagues,

We are excited to announce the "Technical Writing Competition - Pen to Pixel: Writing for the Future of Tech," hosted by the XIM University ACM Student Chapter from the School of Computer Science and Engineering. You are invited to participate in this event and showcase your skills and innovative ideas.

The competition will take place on May 17th, 2023, and will be conducted online for your convenience. You will receive a list of intriguing topics and have 18 hours to craft your write-ups. Submissions will be made through our website. Every participant will receive e-certificates, and the top three winners will be featured on our official ACM website. Additionally, the top two winners will receive prizes and certificates of recognition.

To register for this event and seize this exciting opportunity, please visit our website at [ https://xim-scse.acm.org/EventDetails/PenToPixel ] . Complete the registration process by filling out the provided Google Form [ https://forms.gle/KiUZRsT5TpL3irsq5 ]. Once registered, you will receive all the necessary details for a seamless participation experience.

We look forward to your enthusiastic participation in this remarkable event and wish you the best of luck in your writing endeavors.

For any queries or further information, please reach out to us via email at ucse21015@stu.xim.edu.in.

22/05/2023, 3:00â€¯pm - Smruti Sanjeet (College): Dear Students,

We are in the process of forming a CAS (Career Advisory Services) committee for the academic year 2023-24 and invite interested students to be a part of it. 

Please fill out the form provided in the following link to express your interest: https://forms.gle/V58bFiHBDrrSjqCg8

As a member of the CAS committee, your responsibilities will include:
- Identifying and enlisting potential employers
- Assisting students in preparing for job interviews and writing resumes
- Organizing job fairs and networking events
- Providing support to students struggling to find employment
- Organizing industry talks
- Creating and maintaining a career resources library

By joining the CAS committee, you will have the opportunity to:
- Gain valuable experience in career counseling and placement
- Network with professionals in the IT field
- Learn about the hiring process and improve your job search skills
- Make a difference in the lives of your fellow classmates by helping them find suitable jobs

Please note that after receiving your expression of interest through the form, the school will shortlist candidates for the committee in due course.

Best Wishes
Sripati Mahapatra
